article.headline: Lane scores 27 in North Alabama's 90-84 victory against Queens
article.description: — Jacari Lane's 27 points helped North Alabama defeat Queens 90-84 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Lane scores 27 in North Alabama's 90-84 victory against Queens
article.story: FLORENCE, Ala. -- — Jacari Lane's 27 points helped North Alabama defeat Queens 90-84 on Saturday night. Lane added five assists and three steals for the Lions (9-12, 3-4 Atlantic Sun Conference). KJ Johnson scored 24 points while going 7 of 15 and 8 of 9 from the free-throw line. Dallas Howell had 14 points and was 5-of-7 shooting (4 for 6 from 3-point range). Deyton Albury led the way for the Royals (8-14, 2-5) with 29 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists. Queens also got 18 points and 11 rebounds from BJ McLaurin. In addition, Jacobi Sebock had 14 points and 11 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
